	•	RAI policy and guidelines were revised last year to introduce stricter compliance requirements.
	•	Key touchpoints added include:
	•	Action plans
	•	Stakeholder approvals
	•	Time-bound action steps
	•	Each missed timeline now triggers an escalation, increasing the need for effective tracking.
	•	Portal One provides outdated data (2–3 years old), limiting its usefulness for current tracking.
	•	Portal Two lacks functionality to track the new touchpoints and escalation timelines.
	•	No centralized system exists to monitor progress or flag delays in real-time.